            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/18967",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=doctorrock83",
                        "name": "doctorrock83",
                        "displayName": "julien PAULI",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Patch attached",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=doctorrock83",
                        "name": "doctorrock83",
                        "displayName": "julien PAULI",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-02-08T17:54:34.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-02-08T17:54:34.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/19180",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=peptolab",
                        "name": "peptolab",
                        "displayName": "Simon Mundy",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Hi Julien\n\nI removed it specifically from there as I wanted the ability for the 'FROM' to be applied either by the developer during query creation, or 'just-in-time' before the query is executed. This is handy, as it means that the select object doesn't need to be tied down with a one-to-one relationship with the parent table.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=peptolab",
                        "name": "peptolab",
                        "displayName": "Simon Mundy",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-02-16T20:57:09.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-02-16T20:57:09.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/23618",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=timf",
                        "name": "timf",
                        "displayName": "Tim Fisken",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Although this bug is marked as resolved, it actually is the cause of a number of other bugs listed with Zend_Db_Table_Select.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=timf",
                        "name": "timf",
                        "displayName": "Tim Fisken",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-08-22T16:51:39.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-08-22T16:51:39.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/26495",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=tomas.fejfar@gmail.com",
                        "name": "tomas.fejfar@gmail.com",
                        "displayName": "Tom\u00e1\u0161 Fejfar",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "For me, the expected usage is:\n{code} \n\/\/ Bugs\n$bugs = new Bugs();\n$bugs->select()->where('something = ?',$id); \n\/\/ I want to manipulate the table data - that's why I use the class !\n$bugs->getAdapter()->select()->from('Other_Table')->where('whatever = 1'); \n\/\/ I don't wnat the \"bugs\" included? I'll use the adapter's method\n{code} \nThe present situation is confusing. I create the class because I want to save time and typing when manipulating THIS BUG TABLE, not because I want it to perform *various* DB tasks with it ! ",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=tomas.fejfar@gmail.com",
                        "name": "tomas.fejfar@gmail.com",
                        "displayName": "Tom\u00e1\u0161 Fejfar",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-11-19T10:50:45.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-11-19T10:50:45.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/29305",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dmuir",
                        "name": "dmuir",
                        "displayName": "David Muir",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Agree with Tomas.\nUsing Zend_Db_Table_Select implies you are wanting to select from the given table. If you don't want that, then you should be using Zend_Db_Select instead.\n\nSimon, can you give a reasonable use case where you'd use Zend_Db_Table_Select instead of Zend_Db_Select to select from a table other than the table from which the select came from?\nThis is especially frustrating as the current implementation flips the order of the from and join\n\n{code}\n$bugs = new Bugs();\n$bugs->select()->join('Table2', 'Bugs.id = Table2.bug_id')->where('whatever = 1');\n{code}\nbecomes\n{code:sql}\nSELECT `Bugs`.*\nFROM `Table2`\nINNER JOIN `Bugs`\nWHERE whatever = 1\n{code}\n\nTo fix it you have to specify a from clause explicitly.\n\nWould be good if this issue were reopened and fixed.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dmuir",
                        "name": "dmuir",
                        "displayName": "David Muir",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-03-05T23:00:57.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-03-05T23:00:57.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/33921",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ralph",
                        "name": "ralph",
                        "displayName": "Ralph Schindler",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Since 1.9 there has been a feature in place that allowed select() to be called on a table with that will load the from part into the object.\n\nPlease see [here|http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/manual\/en\/zend.db.table.html#zend.db.table.qry.rows.set.refine.example], and the api doc [here|http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/apidoc\/core\/Zend_Db\/Table\/Zend_Db_Table_Abstract.html#methodselect]\n\nI think it might fix this problem.\n\n-ralph",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ralph",
                        "name": "ralph",
                        "displayName": "Ralph Schindler",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-08-25T17:15:57.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-08-25T17:15:57.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/33935",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=doctorrock83",
                        "name": "doctorrock83",
                        "displayName": "julien PAULI",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "It does, except that you have to explicitly choose it ($table->select(true)), which makes the API look strange.\n\nAnd you have to do that if you want joins to work :\n\n{code}\n$table->select()->setIntegrityCheck(false)->join('other_table', \"$this->_name.mycol = other_table.itscol\", \"some-col\");\n{code}\n\nwon't work and will complain about \"columns mycol not in $this->_name table\".",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=doctorrock83",
                        "name": "doctorrock83",
                        "displayName": "julien PAULI",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-08-26T00:28:52.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-08-26T00:28:52.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/33950",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ralph",
                        "name": "ralph",
                        "displayName": "Ralph Schindler",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "True, but its not something we can change pre 2.0.  Also, to make it more readable, one might consider using:\n\n$table->select(Zend_Db_Table::WITH_FROM_PART)->setItegrityCheck()....\n\nI'd suggest adding these notes to the Zend_Db 2.0 pages in ZFDEV wiki",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ralph",
                        "name": "ralph",
                        "displayName": "Ralph Schindler",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-08-26T07:05:56.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-08-26T07:05:56.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/33967",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=doctorrock83",
                        "name": "doctorrock83",
                        "displayName": "julien PAULI",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "true and right ;-)",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=doctorrock83",
                        "name": "doctorrock83",
                        "displayName": "julien PAULI",
